1
00:00:03,804 --> 00:00:06,340
⟨On the way to find Ryoko's ex-boyfriend Kazuto→

2
00:00:06,574 --> 00:00:11,012
Luna and Ryoko solve the incident that occurred at the base of Tsutenkaku, but...⟩

3
00:00:11,078 --> 00:00:14,515
(Luna) Not at all, you believe in me too much.

4
00:00:14,582 --> 00:00:18,018
⟨Ryoko is confused by Luna's expression that she has never seen before⟩

5
00:00:18,085 --> 00:00:21,021
⟨Another man resembling Kazuto appears→

6
00:00:21,088 --> 00:00:25,593
Luna and Ryoko's story takes an unexpected direction⟩

7
00:00:33,601 --> 00:00:35,536
(sneeze)

8
00:00:35,603 --> 00:00:38,039
(Ryoko) Huh…｡

9
00:00:38,105 --> 00:00:41,042
Oh mom!

10
00:00:41,108 --> 00:00:43,544
(Luna) Ryoko-san…｡

11
00:00:43,611 --> 00:00:46,046
(Ryoko) It was cold, wasn't it?

12
00:00:46,113 --> 00:00:49,049
I just bought some warm meat buns.

13
00:00:49,116 --> 00:00:52,052
Ah, it's pork over here.

14
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:54,054
Let's go back and eat.

15
00:00:54,121 --> 00:00:56,557
(Luna) Ryoko-san.

16
00:00:56,624 --> 00:00:58,559
sorry.

17
00:00:58,626 --> 00:01:02,563
I said something harsh a moment ago.

18
00:01:02,630 --> 00:01:03,998
(Ryoko) Uh-huh.

19
00:01:04,065 --> 00:01:08,502
(Luna) Maybe she was hungry and a little irritated.

20
00:01:08,569 --> 00:01:14,074
(Ryoko) Then, shall we eat pork buns now? While it's warm.

21
00:01:16,077 --> 00:01:19,080
(Luna) It looks delicious. I'll eat it.

22
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:25,519
(Ryoko) Hmm, it's hot.

23
00:01:25,586 --> 00:01:29,023
(Luna) Yeah, it's delicious.

24
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:31,525
(Ryoko) Hehe.

25
00:01:31,592 --> 00:01:34,528
Hey mom.

26
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:37,531
If there's something wrong with me...

27
00:01:37,598 --> 00:01:41,535
Ah, well, there are a lot of things that aren't good.

28
00:01:41,602 --> 00:01:45,606
If you have any concerns, feel free to tell me.

29
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:49,043
(Luna) No.

30
00:01:49,110 --> 00:01:53,547
Even if there was, Ryoko would remain the same...

31
00:01:53,614 --> 00:01:56,617
It's fine as is.

32
00:01:58,619 --> 00:02:01,055
Ah, but only one thing.

33
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:03,991
(Ryoko) What?

34
00:02:04,058 --> 00:02:05,993
(Luna) I talk a little in my sleep.

35
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:09,997
(Ryoko) What!? Am I talking in my sleep?

36
00:02:10,064 --> 00:02:14,502
⟨I wish I could stay like this with mom forever⟩

37
00:02:14,568 --> 00:02:18,005
⟨I walked down the street at night feeling soft and happy⟩

38
00:02:18,072 --> 00:02:22,510
⟨But if there is a beginning, there is also an end⟩

39
00:02:22,576 --> 00:02:25,012
⟨Our journey is coming soon→

40
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:29,517
It was about to end in an unexpected way⟩

41
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:33,587
♪～

42
00:02:40,694 --> 00:02:42,229
(Ryoko) Three more.

43
00:02:42,496 --> 00:02:45,432
What should I do if I still miss the mark after this?

44
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:51,405
(Luna) This list only covers Osaka Prefecture, so let's look up the prefectural borders.

45
00:02:52,740 --> 00:02:55,609
(Ryoko) Ah, there's a kushikatsu restaurant here too.

46
00:02:55,676 --> 00:02:58,612
Kazuto I loved kushikatsu.

47
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:01,115
At that time, it wasn't major yet →

48
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:03,617
They said it would definitely become popular someday.

49
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:06,620
(Luna) So let's talk about Kazuto to the kushikatsu restaurant →

50
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:08,622
Let's ask. (Ryoko) Huh?

51
00:03:08,689 --> 00:03:11,125
(Luna) Do you know “Onihei Hankacho”?

52
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:14,628
This is a popular work by Shotaro Ikenami, who was a foodie.

53
00:03:14,695 --> 00:03:17,631
(Ryoko) Huh? It's a famous historical drama, right? (Luna) Yes.

54
00:03:17,698 --> 00:03:21,635
In "Nippon Kaitoden" which is said to be a side story of "Onihei" →

55
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:25,139
There is a short story called ``The Guest on the Fourth of the New Year''.

56
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:28,642
Soba that is only served once a year at a certain restaurant →

57
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:32,646
It's a story about staking out and catching the culprit who comes to eat here every year.

58
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:36,150
This is an episode about torimono, but I think it can also be applied to searching for people.

59
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:39,153
(Ryoko) What, does that mean Kazuto might come to eat?

60
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,654
(Luna) That's right.

61
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:43,157
By the way, as Ryoko said earlier →

62
00:03:43,223 --> 00:03:45,659
Kushikatsu restaurants became widespread in Osaka →

63
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:47,661
Since the beginning of the 2000s.

64
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:51,665
I loved kushikatsu even before kushikatsu restaurants became popular→

65
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:55,102
A shop that has been in business for over 20 years and is frequented by locals →

66
00:03:55,169 --> 00:03:57,104
It is possible that he was eating it.

67
00:03:57,171 --> 00:04:01,175
If it's your favorite restaurant, you might still be a regular there.

68
00:04:04,178 --> 00:04:07,114
(Ryoko) Ah, 50 years since our founding.

69
00:04:07,181 --> 00:04:09,617
(Tabata) So, what do you want to ask?

70
00:04:09,683 --> 00:04:13,120
(Ryoko) Actually, I'm looking for an old acquaintance.

71
00:04:13,187 --> 00:04:15,122
For this customer →

72
00:04:15,189 --> 00:04:17,625
Is there anyone named Kazuto Sato?

73
00:04:17,691 --> 00:04:19,627
(Tabata) Kazuto Sato?

74
00:04:19,693 --> 00:04:22,630
(Luna) Currently 45 years old and graduated from Eisei University in Tokyo →

75
00:04:22,696 --> 00:04:26,634
I heard that you took over your parents' business after graduating.

76
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:29,637
>> Did that person play baseball in high school?

77
00:04:29,703 --> 00:04:31,138
(Ryoko) Yes!

78
00:04:31,205 --> 00:04:35,142
>> Ah, that's Sato-chan. (Ryoko) Do you know?

79
00:04:35,209 --> 00:04:38,646
>> Long time regular, cram school teacher.

80
00:04:38,712 --> 00:04:43,150
I took over my parents' printing company, but it closed down 10 years ago.

81
00:04:43,217 --> 00:04:46,153
(Ryoko) Ah, Sato Printing!

82
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:48,155
(Luna) I would like to get in touch with this person.

83
00:04:48,222 --> 00:04:51,225
>>Okay, if you really want to, I'll give you a call.

84
00:04:53,227 --> 00:04:55,596
Ah~ Sato-chan.

85
00:04:55,663 --> 00:04:58,098
There are people coming now who want to meet Sato-chan.

86
00:04:58,165 --> 00:05:01,101
Yes, yes, really?

87
00:05:01,168 --> 00:05:03,671
Yeah yeah, hona hona hona hona…｡

88
00:05:05,172 --> 00:05:09,610
I'm heading over here because it's almost lunch time.

89
00:05:09,677 --> 00:05:26,627
♪～

90
00:05:26,694 --> 00:05:30,631
(sound of door opening)

91
00:05:30,698 --> 00:05:37,638
♪～

92
00:05:37,705 --> 00:05:40,708
(Tabata) Oh, Sato-chan, you're so fast!

93
00:05:43,711 --> 00:05:46,213
Hello, I'm Sato!

94
00:05:49,216 --> 00:05:51,652
(Luna) Kazuya Sato…｡

95
00:05:51,719 --> 00:05:55,589
(Sato) I'm sorry. (Ryoko) No, I'm sorry.

96
00:05:55,656 --> 00:05:58,092
>> Well, I might know some of the customers →

97
00:05:58,158 --> 00:06:00,594
Kazuto Sato: I'll ask you.

98
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:04,598
I will also ask the parents of the cram school.

99
00:06:04,665 --> 00:06:07,601
(Ryoko) It won't be that easy...｡

100
00:06:07,668 --> 00:06:10,604
(Luna) But that general seems to have a wide face→

101
00:06:10,671 --> 00:06:13,607
If we can get cooperation from local people →

102
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:17,111
You might be able to find an opportunity to get closer to Kazuto-san.

103
00:06:17,177 --> 00:06:20,114
(Ryoko) (Luna) Oh, are you okay?

104
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:23,117
(Tamura) Noppy. (Luna) Oh, Mr. Tamura.

105
00:06:23,183 --> 00:06:25,619
(Kominato) Hello! Are you looking for someone today?

106
00:06:25,686 --> 00:06:28,622
(Luna) Yes. >> It's tough being out in the cold.

107
00:06:28,689 --> 00:06:30,124
(sneeze)

108
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:34,128
(Luna) Are you sure you're okay? (Ryoko) Something is giving me chills right now.

109
00:06:34,194 --> 00:06:36,630
(Luna) Do you have a headache or sore throat?

110
00:06:36,697 --> 00:06:39,633
(Ryoko) Ah...my head might hurt a bit.

111
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:41,702
(Luna) Excuse me.

112
00:06:43,203 --> 00:06:45,639
It's 37 degrees and 4 minutes.

113
00:06:45,706 --> 00:06:49,143
>> Do you understand? Do you have a bad cold?

114
00:06:49,209 --> 00:06:52,146
(Tamura) Shall I introduce you to the clinic I go to?

115
00:06:52,212 --> 00:06:54,081
(Ryoko) Ah, it's okay, it's no big deal.

116
00:06:54,148 --> 00:06:56,083
(Luna) Let's go home and relax today.

117
00:06:56,150 --> 00:07:00,587
>> Ah, that's better. There's a cold wave coming.

118
00:07:00,654 --> 00:07:03,590
(Tamura) Hello, I would like a taxi please.

119
00:07:03,657 --> 00:07:05,092
>> I'm sorry.

120
00:07:05,159 --> 00:07:07,594
I'd like to drop you off by car because it's Yamayama.→

121
00:07:07,661 --> 00:07:10,664
Ordinary people will get angry if you ride it.

122
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:15,102
(Tamura) I just called a taxi and it looks like it will come soon.

123
00:07:15,169 --> 00:07:18,105
(Luna) Thank you for your help.

124
00:07:18,172 --> 00:07:22,109
(Tamura) If you don't mind, we'll be traveling by car all day today.

125
00:07:22,176 --> 00:07:25,179
(Ryoko) No, that's it... (Luna) I'll borrow it.

126
00:07:27,181 --> 00:07:30,617
(Ryoko) Ah, I'm sorry...

127
00:07:30,684 --> 00:07:33,620
(Tamura) Oh, it suits you.

128
00:07:33,687 --> 00:07:36,123
>>Haha, what are you, handsome?

129
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:38,625
(Sound of something being taken out of pocket) If you'd like this.

130
00:07:38,692 --> 00:07:40,627
(Ryoko) Ah, it's okay.

131
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:42,629
>> That's right.

132
00:07:42,696 --> 00:07:44,631
(Tamura) Well then, take care.

133
00:07:44,698 --> 00:07:46,700
(Ryoko) Thank you very much.

134
00:07:49,203 --> 00:07:52,139
>> What's the matter? You're traveling by car all day today.

135
00:07:52,206 --> 00:07:55,075
I'll be outside forever after this.

136
00:07:55,142 --> 00:07:58,078
(Ryoko) >> Is Cairo there?

137
00:07:58,145 --> 00:08:00,147
(Tamura) It's okay. >> Isn't it?

138
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:07,154
(Luna) Please contact the person at Tsutenkaku.

139
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:19,600
♪～

140
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,602
(sound of door closing)

141
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:23,604
Looking for someone?

142
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:26,106
(Tabata) Why did you come all the way from Tokyo?

143
00:08:26,173 --> 00:08:28,108
This is it though.

144
00:08:28,175 --> 00:08:30,611
There are so many Beppin girls that their eyeballs are about to pop out.

145
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:33,113
I hope I can help somehow.

146
00:08:33,180 --> 00:08:36,617
General, I have a weakness for beautiful women, so who are you looking for?

147
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:40,621
Ah~ My name is Kazuto Sato, 45 years old.

148
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:44,625
Graduated from Eisei University in Tokyo. Played baseball during high school →

149
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:47,628
Apparently, his family runs a business in Osaka.

150
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:49,630
(Customer) There are a lot of Mr. Sato.

151
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,198
that….

152
00:08:54,635 --> 00:08:56,570
(Kiwako) Then please come here.

153
00:08:56,637 --> 00:08:59,139
Thank you very much. Thank you very much.

154
00:09:02,643 --> 00:09:04,578
Hello. Hello.

155
00:09:04,645 --> 00:09:07,581
Kanade! what happened? What about school?

156
00:09:07,648 --> 00:09:09,650
Did something happen?

157
00:09:17,658 --> 00:09:22,095
I came here too. Huh? So?

158
00:09:22,162 --> 00:09:24,598
Thank you for coming home.

159
00:09:24,665 --> 00:09:27,601
What did you talk about? >> Nothing.

160
00:09:27,668 --> 00:09:29,603
Why?

161
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:32,105
You don't have to think too much.

162
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:35,108
But... >> Hey, it's better than that →

163
00:09:35,175 --> 00:09:38,612
Can you pick up the cleaning on the way home?

164
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:40,681
As for the exchange ticket...

165
00:09:42,683 --> 00:09:46,186
(thermometer alarm)

166
00:09:48,188 --> 00:09:50,624
(Ryoko) 37 degrees 4 minutes.

167
00:09:50,691 --> 00:09:53,126
Mom, that's a big hit.

168
00:09:53,193 --> 00:09:56,129
(Luna) Are you sure you don't have to go to the hospital?

169
00:09:56,196 --> 00:09:59,633
(Ryoko) If you feel like this, I think you'll get better if you sleep.

170
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,702
(Luna) Yes.

171
00:10:03,203 --> 00:10:06,139
(Ryoko) Mr. Tamura is really a nice person.

172
00:10:06,206 --> 00:10:10,143
(Luna) There are actually men who lend their coats to women.

173
00:10:10,210 --> 00:10:14,648
I thought it was only in girls' manga.

174
00:10:14,715 --> 00:10:18,652
(Ryoko) No, not really.

175
00:10:18,719 --> 00:10:22,155
My husband also lent me his jacket once.

176
00:10:22,222 --> 00:10:24,658
When we were dating.

177
00:10:24,725 --> 00:10:28,161
(Luna) You're so kind, sir.

178
00:10:28,228 --> 00:10:32,666
(Ryoko) That's what I thought when I got married.

179
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:36,670
(Luna) Maybe it's better to trust your intuition.

180
00:10:36,737 --> 00:10:38,672
(Ryoko) Huh?

181
00:10:38,739 --> 00:10:42,242
(Luna) Well, I'll go buy some medicine.

182
00:10:46,246 --> 00:10:49,182
(Aromatic) Huh... (Atsushi) I'm home.

183
00:10:49,249 --> 00:10:51,184
(Atsushi) What?

184
00:10:51,251 --> 00:10:54,621
(Aromatic) An article about my mother when she was young.

185
00:10:54,688 --> 00:10:56,623
(Atsushi) Young!

186
00:10:56,690 --> 00:11:00,127
What is it? It's obvious, but →

187
00:11:00,193 --> 00:11:03,130
I guess your mother had her youth too.

188
00:11:03,196 --> 00:11:06,133
Eh, what is that?

189
00:11:06,199 --> 00:11:08,635
(cough cough)

190
00:11:08,702 --> 00:11:11,638
Mom, when will you come home?

191
00:11:11,705 --> 00:11:15,709
Huh... It's impossible to take care of a cat.

192
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:21,148
Did she run away with a man?

193
00:11:21,214 --> 00:11:25,152
That's not true. >> Can you say that?

194
00:11:25,218 --> 00:11:29,156
There's probably a lot of things we don't know about.

195
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:31,725
Both mom and dad.

196
00:11:41,234 --> 00:11:57,117
♪～

197
00:11:57,184 --> 00:11:59,119
(Ryoko) Ah...｡

198
00:11:59,186 --> 00:12:01,121
(Luna's voice) "I'm going out for a while.

199
00:12:01,188 --> 00:12:04,624
I made some porridge, so please warm it up and eat it.

200
00:12:04,691 --> 00:12:07,127
Take medicine so it doesn't hurt your stomach →

201
00:12:07,194 --> 00:12:10,630
Please drink it with plenty of water."

202
00:12:10,697 --> 00:12:13,700
(Ryoko) Thank you, Mom.

203
00:12:22,709 --> 00:12:32,652
📱(ringtone)

204
00:12:32,719 --> 00:12:34,654
(Haruko) Hello.

205
00:12:34,721 --> 00:12:38,658
(Ryoko) Hello, mom? 📱 How are you doing?

206
00:12:38,725 --> 00:12:41,161
(Ryoko) I caught a cold. 📱 Oh no.

207
00:12:41,228 --> 00:12:43,163
Flu? Are you okay?

208
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:46,166
(Ryoko) I don't have that much of a fever, so it's okay.

209
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:48,168
How about that?

210
00:12:48,235 --> 00:12:51,171
>>Yes, school started yesterday.

211
00:12:51,238 --> 00:12:54,107
It's been a while since I've made a bento.

212
00:12:54,174 --> 00:12:57,110
(Ryoko) Don't those girls have a cheeky mouth?

213
00:12:57,177 --> 00:13:03,116
📱 Well, Yoshika is talkative and Atsushi is unfriendly.

214
00:13:03,183 --> 00:13:06,119
📱 But at heart they are both really good kids.

215
00:13:06,186 --> 00:13:10,123
📱 I'm worried about you too.

216
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:12,692
Please come back as soon as possible.

217
00:13:14,194 --> 00:13:16,630
(Ryoko) How is Kikuo-san?

218
00:13:16,696 --> 00:13:19,132
>> Looks like he's busy as usual.

219
00:13:19,199 --> 00:13:22,135
Also, I haven't been feeling well for some reason.

220
00:13:22,202 --> 00:13:26,139
📱 Isn't Kikuo-san lonely too?

221
00:13:26,206 --> 00:13:28,208
(Ryoko) How is it?

222
00:13:29,709 --> 00:13:32,646
I'll contact you again then.

223
00:13:32,712 --> 00:13:42,155
♪～

224
00:13:42,222 --> 00:13:45,659
(Sound of door opening) (Sound) Mom.

225
00:13:45,725 --> 00:13:47,661
(Kiwako) Did you come again?

226
00:13:47,727 --> 00:13:50,230
(footsteps)

227
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:57,671
you….

228
00:14:12,986 --> 00:14:15,922
(Ryoko's voice) ``Mom, the porridge was delicious.

229
00:14:15,989 --> 00:14:19,492
Thank you very much.”

230
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:35,508
(Luna's voice) "My time with the princess is almost over."

231
00:14:54,961 --> 00:14:56,897
>> Huh…｡

232
00:15:10,477 --> 00:15:12,979
(Sound of electricity turning on) (Kikuo) Ah.

233
00:15:15,982 --> 00:15:20,420
Welcome back. Thank you for your hard work.

234
00:15:20,487 --> 00:15:23,923
(Kikuo) Did I wake you up? Sorry.

235
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:27,927
There's some meat in the fridge, so warm it up and eat it.

236
00:15:27,994 --> 00:15:31,431
Thank you as always. >> Bye.

237
00:15:31,498 --> 00:15:33,500
Ah, mother-in-law.

238
00:15:35,001 --> 00:15:37,504
Do you have a moment?

239
00:15:43,009 --> 00:15:46,946
(Ryoko) Ah, this soup is delicious too.

240
00:15:47,013 --> 00:15:49,950
Thanks to mom, I'm feeling better.

241
00:15:50,016 --> 00:15:53,953
(Luna) Please don't push yourself too hard. (Ryoko) Yeah.

242
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:56,890
Just in case, I'll take some medicine.

243
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,392
(Luna) Ah, when I take medicine...

244
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:02,896
(Ryoko) Be sure to drink plenty of water, right?

245
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,464
(Luna) Yes.

246
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:11,905
I would like to ask you something again.

247
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,907
(Ryoko) What?

248
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:19,412
(Luna) Ryoko-san, do you want to meet Kazuto-san?

249
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:22,916
(Ryoko) Huh? Is that a question now?

250
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:25,485
(Luna) I just wanted to confirm.

251
00:16:27,487 --> 00:16:29,489
(Ryoko) I want to see you.

252
00:16:31,991 --> 00:16:35,929
Actually, yesterday me too →

253
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:40,934
I was thinking the same thing in bed.

254
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:46,439
I want it to end properly.

255
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:48,441
(Luna) Do you want it to end?

256
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:54,881
(Ryoko) To tell you the truth, yesterday I just wanted to go back to Tokyo for a moment.

257
00:16:54,948 --> 00:16:57,884
But even if I go back like this→

258
00:16:57,951 --> 00:17:02,455
It's the same thing happening again.

259
00:17:03,957 --> 00:17:06,893
Every time I have something to do with my family→

260
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:10,897
What are these people so angry?

261
00:17:10,964 --> 00:17:14,467
I always remembered Kazuto.

262
00:17:16,970 --> 00:17:21,975
I told you about how I ignored your last phone call, right?

263
00:17:23,476 --> 00:17:27,981
I've always regretted that time.

264
00:17:30,483 --> 00:17:34,988
I wonder what Kazuto wanted to convey.

265
00:17:36,489 --> 00:17:40,427
In order to say goodbye to myself from that day →

266
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:44,497
I think I want to know the truth.

267
00:17:45,999 --> 00:17:48,935
(Luna) Clear up the grievances you've been holding on →

268
00:17:49,002 --> 00:17:52,439
Does that mean you want to move forward?

269
00:17:52,505 --> 00:17:56,509
(Ryoko) Yeah. (Luna) I understand.

270
00:17:58,511 --> 00:18:01,448
Let's go. (Ryoko) Huh?

271
00:18:01,514 --> 00:18:11,958
♪～

272
00:18:12,025 --> 00:18:14,027
(Ryoko) Mom?

273
00:18:19,532 --> 00:18:21,468
(Ryoko) Huh...｡

274
00:18:21,534 --> 00:18:33,980
♪～

275
00:18:34,047 --> 00:18:36,049
(Ryoko) Kazuto...｡

276
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:39,552
(Luna) Kanade-san.

277
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:50,063
(Luna) Sorry, I'm late. (Play) No.

278
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:56,436
Ryoko, right?

279
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:58,938
(Ryoko) Ah, yes.

280
00:18:59,005 --> 00:19:03,009
>> Nice to meet you, my name is Kanade Sato.

281
00:19:04,511 --> 00:19:06,446
I wanted to meet you.

282
00:19:06,513 --> 00:19:08,515
(Ryoko) Eh...｡

283
00:19:10,517 --> 00:19:14,020
>> My house is right next to you, so I'll show you around.

284
00:19:22,529 --> 00:19:24,964
(Luna) Ryoko-san.

285
00:19:25,031 --> 00:19:27,534
(Ryoko) Yeah...｡

286
00:19:29,035 --> 00:19:35,475
⟨This day finally came before I was even mentally prepared⟩

287
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:40,480
⟨I wonder what will happen if I see Kazuto's face⟩

288
00:19:40,547 --> 00:19:42,482
⟨scared⟩

289
00:19:42,549 --> 00:19:46,052
⟨But I want to meet you⟩

290
00:19:57,897 --> 00:20:00,400
(sound of breathing)

291
00:20:08,508 --> 00:20:10,510
>>Mother.

292
00:20:16,015 --> 00:20:17,951
(Kiwako) Ryoko-san.

293
00:20:18,017 --> 00:20:23,022
It's been a while.My name is Kiwako Sato.

294
00:20:38,972 --> 00:20:44,978
(footsteps)

295
00:20:49,482 --> 00:20:51,484
(Sound of placing a teacup)

296
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:59,425
Ryoko →

297
00:20:59,492 --> 00:21:03,997
I've always wanted to apologize to you.

298
00:21:05,999 --> 00:21:09,435
Kazuto is...→

299
00:21:09,502 --> 00:21:14,440
My younger brother was 23 years ago→

300
00:21:14,507 --> 00:21:18,444
4 months after breaking up with Ryoko →

301
00:21:18,511 --> 00:21:20,513
He passed away.

302
00:21:22,515 --> 00:21:24,951
(Kiwako) Winter of 4th year of university →

303
00:21:25,018 --> 00:21:29,956
I was diagnosed with terminal cancer at the hospital where I was admitted for burns →

304
00:21:30,023 --> 00:21:33,393
I was told that I only had six months to live.

305
00:21:33,459 --> 00:21:36,896
I'm only 22 years old.

306
00:21:36,963 --> 00:21:39,899
From now on...

307
00:21:39,966 --> 00:21:45,405
It seems like he himself had a hard time accepting it.

308
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:49,909
The thing about not telling anyone about your illness is →

309
00:21:49,976 --> 00:21:52,912
That was the conclusion my brother came to.

310
00:21:52,979 --> 00:21:56,983
Also to Ryoko, who I was dating.

311
00:21:58,484 --> 00:22:01,421
(Kiwako) [Do you mean to play a fake lover? ]

312
00:22:01,487 --> 00:22:06,926
(Custom) [She is aiming for the Olympics in badminton]

313
00:22:06,993 --> 00:22:14,934
[Now that I have been selected as a training player, this is the most important moment for me]

314
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:17,437
[I don't want to disturb you]

315
00:22:17,503 --> 00:22:19,939
[That's no good]

316
00:22:20,006 --> 00:22:22,442
[Please, sister]

317
00:22:22,508 --> 00:22:29,015
[I want her to always smile]

318
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:35,388
(Custom) [My love for you is gone]

319
00:22:35,455 --> 00:22:40,460
[I will live with her]

320
00:22:44,464 --> 00:22:49,402
(Kiwako's voice) Although I once decided to respect my brother's feelings→

321
00:22:49,469 --> 00:22:51,904
When I see that face →

322
00:22:51,971 --> 00:22:55,475
I guess this is wrong after all.

323
00:22:58,478 --> 00:23:04,417
I did something terrible to Ryoko too...

324
00:23:04,484 --> 00:23:07,920
I've been curious about it for a long time.

325
00:23:07,987 --> 00:23:13,493
I'm really sorry.

326
00:23:16,496 --> 00:23:18,498
(Ryoko) Huh...｡

327
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:53,900
(Ryoko) After we broke up, I got a phone call.

328
00:23:53,966 --> 00:23:58,971
Can we meet one last time?

329
00:24:00,973 --> 00:24:06,412
But I can't believe it's the true end →

330
00:24:06,479 --> 00:24:08,981
You don't think so, do you?

331
00:24:10,483 --> 00:24:16,422
Haha, I'm the worst.

332
00:24:16,489 --> 00:24:19,425
Ha...

333
00:24:19,492 --> 00:24:23,496
Ha~ ha...

334
00:24:25,998 --> 00:24:27,934
(Luna) Ryoko! (Kiwako) Ryoko!

335
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:30,002
(Luna) Ryoko!

336
00:24:37,143 --> 00:24:40,580
(Kiwako's voice) Ryoko-san, are you okay?

337
00:24:40,646 --> 00:24:43,082
(Luna) If you don't mind →

338
00:24:43,149 --> 00:24:46,085
Can I rest here for a little while?

339
00:24:46,152 --> 00:24:48,154
>> Of course.

340
00:24:51,157 --> 00:24:55,661
(Kiwako) I shouldn't have gotten into that kind of play after all.

341
00:24:57,163 --> 00:25:04,103
(Luna) That's a way of breaking up that appears in Osamu Dazai's works.

342
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:06,606
>> Huh?

343
00:25:06,672 --> 00:25:11,110
(Luna) An unfinished work that became Dazai Sensei's posthumous work →

344
00:25:11,177 --> 00:25:15,114
For the main character to break up with his mistress →

345
00:25:15,181 --> 00:25:20,052
This is a story about a woman he knows pretending to be his wife.

346
00:25:20,119 --> 00:25:24,056
The title is "Good Bye."

347
00:25:24,123 --> 00:25:26,058
>> "Good bye"...

348
00:25:26,125 --> 00:25:29,629
[Haa haa haa…]

349
00:25:34,634 --> 00:25:39,071
(Sound) I know that piece.

350
00:25:39,138 --> 00:25:42,575
There are a lot of novels in my uncle's room →

351
00:25:42,642 --> 00:25:45,578
I read that sometimes.

352
00:25:45,645 --> 00:25:48,581
(Luna) Kazuto's room...

353
00:25:48,648 --> 00:26:05,097
♪～

354
00:26:05,164 --> 00:26:07,166
>>This.

355
00:26:08,668 --> 00:26:11,103
Is it a substitute for a bookmark?

356
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:13,105
That Ryoko-san →

357
00:26:13,172 --> 00:26:16,609
I thought it must be my ex-girlfriend.

358
00:26:19,612 --> 00:26:23,049
This room is calming.

359
00:26:23,115 --> 00:26:29,055
I always come here when I have something to worry about.

360
00:26:29,121 --> 00:26:33,559
So I started reading a book that caught my eye →

361
00:26:33,626 --> 00:26:36,629
The answer I wanted was written there.

362
00:26:38,130 --> 00:26:41,067
He died shortly before I was born.

363
00:26:41,133 --> 00:26:44,570
I don't have any direct memories of it.

364
00:26:44,637 --> 00:26:50,076
I feel strangely close to my uncle.

365
00:26:50,142 --> 00:27:05,591
♪～

366
00:27:05,658 --> 00:27:08,160
(Luna) Marginaria...｡

367
00:27:14,667 --> 00:27:17,036
>> Ryoko-san.

368
00:27:17,103 --> 00:27:20,039
How are you doing?

369
00:27:20,106 --> 00:27:22,041
Can I eat udon?

370
00:27:22,108 --> 00:27:25,544
(Ryoko) Ah, sorry.

371
00:27:25,611 --> 00:27:32,118
>> I'm really grateful to Ryoko for coming.

372
00:27:33,619 --> 00:27:38,557
Luna-san and Kanade came with me yesterday...

373
00:27:38,624 --> 00:27:45,064
(Luna) [In other words, you told a kind lie for Ryoko-san]

374
00:27:45,131 --> 00:27:49,568
[I think that feeling is very precious]

375
00:27:49,635 --> 00:27:53,072
[But even now, 23 years later→

376
00:27:53,139 --> 00:27:58,644
Ryoko is suffering from the memories of that time.

377
00:28:00,646 --> 00:28:04,583
>> [My uncle is Ryoko-san →

378
00:28:04,650 --> 00:28:07,153
I wanted you to be happy, right? ]

379
00:28:08,654 --> 00:28:13,592
I was told that I should tell you the truth →

380
00:28:13,659 --> 00:28:16,162
My heart was shaken.

381
00:28:19,098 --> 00:28:24,537
(Ryoko) Kanade-san looks just like Kazuto-san.

382
00:28:24,603 --> 00:28:29,542
>> Not just her face, but also her kind side →

383
00:28:29,608 --> 00:28:32,545
It's a little delicate but has a strong core.

384
00:28:32,611 --> 00:28:35,114
I feel nervous sometimes.

385
00:28:37,116 --> 00:28:40,553
(Kiwako's voice) I'm a single mother.

386
00:28:40,619 --> 00:28:45,057
The people around me strongly opposed my decision to become an unmarried mother.

387
00:28:45,124 --> 00:28:48,060
Kazuto was the only one who supported me.

388
00:28:48,127 --> 00:28:52,631
It was thanks to Kazuto that I was able to meet Kanade.

389
00:28:55,134 --> 00:28:58,070
Ah, sorry for all the unnecessary chatter.

390
00:28:58,137 --> 00:29:00,573
Ryoko-san probably isn't in good health either.

391
00:29:00,639 --> 00:29:03,075
Please stay the night today.

392
00:29:03,142 --> 00:29:06,078
(Ryoko) No, I can't afford to cause you such trouble...

393
00:29:06,145 --> 00:29:09,582
(Luna) Ryoko-san. (Ryoko) Mama.

394
00:29:09,648 --> 00:29:12,585
(Luna) I'll take your word for it here.

395
00:29:12,651 --> 00:29:15,087
Thank you very much Kiwako-san.

396
00:29:15,154 --> 00:29:17,022
>> Yes.

397
00:29:17,089 --> 00:29:28,534
♪～

398
00:29:28,601 --> 00:29:30,536
Excuse me.

399
00:29:30,603 --> 00:29:33,038
Isn't it cold?

400
00:29:33,105 --> 00:29:37,610
Please use this if you like. (Ryoko) Ah, thank you.

401
00:29:39,111 --> 00:29:42,548
>> Old wooden houses get cold, right?

402
00:29:42,615 --> 00:29:46,118
Please stay warm. (Ryoko) Yes.

403
00:29:51,123 --> 00:29:55,060
(Custom) [My parents' house is made of wood, so it's cold in winter.]

404
00:29:55,127 --> 00:29:59,064
(Ryoko) [But I long for a detached house with a garden.]

405
00:29:59,131 --> 00:30:02,067
>> [I used to climb trees a lot when I was little]

406
00:30:02,134 --> 00:30:05,070
(Ryoko) [Is there such a big tree? 〕 >> 〔Yes〕

407
00:30:05,137 --> 00:30:08,073
[Please come and see it next time. I want to introduce it to my family.]

408
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:10,075
(Ryoko) [Is it okay? 〕 >> 〔Of course〕

409
00:30:10,142 --> 00:30:11,577
(Ryoko) [I want to go! ]

410
00:30:11,644 --> 00:30:14,647
>> [I think everyone will be happy] (Ryoko) [Looking forward to it! ]

411
00:30:16,148 --> 00:30:51,550
♪～

412
00:30:51,617 --> 00:30:55,621
(birds chirping)

413
00:31:00,626 --> 00:31:02,561
good morning.

414
00:31:02,628 --> 00:31:04,563
That this...

415
00:31:04,630 --> 00:31:07,066
(Luna) Thank you.

416
00:31:07,132 --> 00:31:27,519
♪～

417
00:31:27,586 --> 00:31:29,521
(Luna) 《Gentle lie...》

418
00:31:29,588 --> 00:31:33,025
>> [Ryoko-san wanted someone to be happy, right? ]

419
00:31:33,092 --> 00:31:35,027
(Luna) 《Declaration of life expectancy...》

420
00:31:35,094 --> 00:31:37,029
>> [I was diagnosed with terminal cancer...]

421
00:31:37,096 --> 00:31:41,533
(Ryoko) [You don't think it's the true end, do you?]

422
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:44,036
(Luna) 《The novel left behind...》

423
00:31:44,103 --> 00:31:48,040
(Sound) [I thought it must have been his ex-girlfriend]

424
00:31:48,107 --> 00:31:50,042
(Luna)《Osamu Dazai...》

425
00:31:50,109 --> 00:31:53,545
>> [I feel close to my uncle]

426
00:31:53,612 --> 00:32:01,053
♪～

427
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:03,122
(Luna) We are connected.

428
00:32:08,494 --> 00:32:10,929
(Luna) Good morning.

429
00:32:10,996 --> 00:32:13,432
How are you feeling?

430
00:32:13,499 --> 00:32:17,436
(Ryoko) Yeah, it's gotten a lot better. (Luna) I'm glad.

431
00:32:17,503 --> 00:32:21,507
Could you please come with me?

432
00:32:50,536 --> 00:32:52,471
(Ryoko) What?

433
00:32:52,538 --> 00:32:54,973
(Luna) Kazuto was alive →

434
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:59,411
It seems that he read books using a reading method called Marginalia.

435
00:32:59,478 --> 00:33:01,413
(Ryoko) Marji...?

436
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:05,918
(Luna) My thoughts and questions in the margins of the book →

437
00:33:05,984 --> 00:33:09,421
This is a reading technique in which you write notes etc.

438
00:33:09,488 --> 00:33:12,991
It was also used by Natsume Soseki.

439
00:33:20,499 --> 00:33:22,434
(Ryoko) Ah.

440
00:33:22,501 --> 00:33:25,437
(Luna) And Osamu Dazai's works →

441
00:33:25,504 --> 00:33:29,441
There were a lot of posts in particular.

442
00:33:29,508 --> 00:33:31,510
For example, here.

443
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:44,523
(Custom voice) "I only have a short time left to live."

444
00:33:52,531 --> 00:33:54,967
(Custom voice) "It's a self-produced lie."

445
00:33:55,034 --> 00:33:57,469
“What would I do?”

446
00:33:57,536 --> 00:34:12,918
♪～

447
00:34:12,985 --> 00:34:16,422
(Custom voice) ``I will make you hate me and forget me once and for all.''

448
00:34:16,488 --> 00:34:19,992
[I no longer have any love for you]

449
00:34:22,494 --> 00:34:26,432
(Luna) And the last thing Kazuto was reading was probably →

450
00:34:26,498 --> 00:34:29,001
This is the work.

451
00:34:33,005 --> 00:34:34,940
(Luna) "Pandora's Box".

452
00:34:35,007 --> 00:34:37,443
A young man with tuberculosis →

453
00:34:37,509 --> 00:34:42,014
This is a story about living cheerfully despite the fear of approaching death.

454
00:34:49,021 --> 00:34:53,459
(Luna) My physical strength is low and it's hard to even hold a pen→

455
00:34:53,525 --> 00:34:56,528
I think he kept writing.

456
00:35:03,969 --> 00:35:06,905
(Custom voice) “It’s time to decide whether to die or live →

457
00:35:06,972 --> 00:35:09,908
It doesn't seem to be the key to determining a person's happiness or unhappiness.

458
00:35:09,975 --> 00:35:12,911
I'm starting to feel like that.'' >> [coughing]

459
00:35:12,978 --> 00:35:15,414
(Custom voice) “What is dedication?

460
00:35:15,481 --> 00:35:19,918
It is the most brilliant way to make the most of it forever.

461
00:35:19,985 --> 00:35:25,491
Man is immortal only through this pure devotion."

462
00:35:26,992 --> 00:35:31,497
(Custom voice) ``Eternal love, the feeling of caring for others.''

463
00:35:40,005 --> 00:35:42,441
(Custom voice) “Everyone in the world →

464
00:35:42,508 --> 00:35:45,444
If only it were as simple as Kappore-san→

465
00:35:45,511 --> 00:35:50,015
It made me think that the world would definitely become a better place to live in."

466
00:35:52,518 --> 00:35:57,523
(Customer's voice) ``Instead of worrying and suffering, live with a bright outlook.''

467
00:36:01,460 --> 00:36:04,897
(Customer's voice) ``For those who live side by side with death→

468
00:36:04,963 --> 00:36:10,469
The smile of a single flower is more ingrained in my heart than the issue of life and death.''

469
00:36:18,977 --> 00:36:21,413
[Sound of sipping]

470
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:25,984
(Customer's voice) ``Even if I can't see you, I can still remember your smile like a flower.''

471
00:36:34,493 --> 00:36:38,430
(Custom voice) “Humans have been pushed into the depths of unhappiness→

472
00:36:38,497 --> 00:36:43,936
Even though I'm rolling around, someday I'll find a ray of hope →

473
00:36:44,002 --> 00:36:47,005
I'm just trying to find it by my fingers."

474
00:36:48,507 --> 00:36:52,511
(Customer's voice) ``I want you to find someone who feels the same way.''

475
00:36:55,514 --> 00:36:59,885
(Custom voice) ``Let's walk straight at a very natural pace.''

476
00:36:59,952 --> 00:37:03,388
Where does this road lead?

477
00:37:03,455 --> 00:37:06,892
It's like a growing vine →

478
00:37:06,959 --> 00:37:08,894
You had better listen.

479
00:37:08,961 --> 00:37:10,896
The vine will answer.

480
00:37:10,963 --> 00:37:13,398
“I don’t know anything.

481
00:37:13,465 --> 00:37:18,971
However, it seems that the sun is shining in the direction in which it grows.''

482
00:37:23,976 --> 00:37:28,981
(Customer's voice) "I'm sure Ryoko will be fine."

483
00:37:33,485 --> 00:37:37,422
(Custom voice) ``You are reading the story of Pandora's Box from Greek mythology.

484
00:37:37,489 --> 00:37:39,424
You probably know.

485
00:37:39,491 --> 00:37:42,928
Just like opening a box that shouldn't be opened →

486
00:37:42,995 --> 00:37:47,933
Sickness, sorrow, jealousy, greed→

487
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:53,438
Suspicion, insidiousness, hunger, hatred, etc.→

488
00:37:53,505 --> 00:37:56,441
All kinds of bad luck insects are crawling out →

489
00:37:56,508 --> 00:37:58,877
Covering the sky and flying around →

490
00:37:58,944 --> 00:38:01,380
Since then, humans →

491
00:38:01,446 --> 00:38:04,883
I had to writhe in misery forever →

492
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:07,886
But in the corner of that box →

493
00:38:07,953 --> 00:38:11,390
A small shiny stone the size of a poppy grain remains →

494
00:38:11,456 --> 00:38:17,462
It is said that the word ``hope'' was faintly written on the stone.''

495
00:38:18,964 --> 00:38:21,967
(Custom voice) ``Have hope until the end.''

496
00:38:23,468 --> 00:38:25,470
(Ryoko) Hope…｡

497
00:38:26,972 --> 00:38:28,907
📱(Custom) [This is Kazuto]

498
00:38:28,974 --> 00:38:32,911
📱〔Before I go to Osaka, there is something I really want to meet and tell you.〕

499
00:38:32,978 --> 00:38:36,415
📱〔I'll be waiting in the library tomorrow〕

500
00:38:36,481 --> 00:39:06,878
♪～

501
00:39:06,945 --> 00:39:10,882
(Custom voice) "Thank you, Ryoko."

502
00:39:10,949 --> 00:39:16,888
♪～

503
00:39:16,955 --> 00:39:18,957
(Ryoko) Huh…｡

504
00:39:23,462 --> 00:39:26,398
(cry)

505
00:39:26,465 --> 00:39:42,414
♪～

506
00:39:42,481 --> 00:40:02,367
(cry)

507
00:40:02,434 --> 00:40:03,869
(cry)

508
00:40:03,935 --> 00:40:19,384
♪～

509
00:40:19,451 --> 00:40:23,388
(Kiwako) Kazuto Ryoko came.

510
00:40:23,455 --> 00:40:46,912
♪～

511
00:40:46,978 --> 00:40:49,915
(Luna) Thank you, Kiwako-san.

512
00:40:49,981 --> 00:40:51,983
>> Welcome.

513
00:40:59,491 --> 00:41:03,428
Ryoko-san, please hold this.

514
00:41:03,495 --> 00:41:05,997
(Ryoko) Thank you.

515
00:41:12,003 --> 00:41:13,939
(Ryoko) Mama.

516
00:41:14,005 --> 00:41:18,944
I'm glad you brought me to Osaka.

517
00:41:19,010 --> 00:41:23,014
It was nice to meet Kazuto.

518
00:41:25,016 --> 00:41:31,456
Tomorrow, I thought, I should look forward and start living properly again.

519
00:41:31,523 --> 00:41:35,460
thanks so much.

520
00:41:35,527 --> 00:41:38,029
It's all thanks to mom.

521
00:41:39,531 --> 00:41:43,034
(Luna) Thank you very much, Ryoko-san.

522
00:41:45,036 --> 00:41:49,474
I have somewhere to stop by, so could you please go back to the hotel first?

523
00:41:49,541 --> 00:41:51,476
(Ryoko) Yes.

524
00:41:51,543 --> 00:42:12,931
♪～

525
00:42:12,998 --> 00:42:16,935
📱(Identification sound)

526
00:42:17,002 --> 00:42:19,938
📱(Voice guidance) I can't answer the phone right now.

527
00:42:20,005 --> 00:42:24,943
📱 After the beep, please tell us what you need.

528
00:42:25,010 --> 00:42:27,445
📱(tone)

529
00:42:27,512 --> 00:42:32,450
(Ryoko) Mr. Kikuo, I will return to Tokyo tonight.

530
00:42:32,517 --> 00:42:36,955
I want to talk to you properly when I get back.

531
00:42:37,022 --> 00:42:43,461
I've been running away from important things for a long time.

532
00:42:43,528 --> 00:42:49,034
From now on, I want to focus on my family.

533
00:42:51,036 --> 00:42:53,538
I'll contact you again.

534
00:43:00,979 --> 00:43:02,480
(Ryoko) Ah.

535
00:43:03,982 --> 00:43:07,419
(Tamura) Sorry to bother you. (Ryoko) Thank you very much.

536
00:43:07,485 --> 00:43:09,421
(Tamura) I'm glad you're back in shape.

537
00:43:09,487 --> 00:43:13,491
(Ryoko) Haha... Yes, thank you for all your help.

538
00:43:14,993 --> 00:43:19,431
(Tamura) Ryoko-san, please tell us about Noppy.

539
00:43:19,497 --> 00:43:21,933
(Ryoko) Yes. (Tamura) That guy→

540
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:24,936
I may think I'm being strong, but →

541
00:43:25,003 --> 00:43:27,939
From my point of view, it's very dangerous.

542
00:43:28,006 --> 00:43:29,941
(Ryoko) Is it dangerous? (Tamura) Yeah.

543
00:43:30,008 --> 00:43:32,944
It's been that way since high school.

544
00:43:33,011 --> 00:43:36,448
If something happens, please help me.

545
00:43:36,514 --> 00:43:38,950
(Ryoko) Yes.

546
00:43:39,017 --> 00:43:44,456
Mom is happy because she has good friends.

547
00:43:44,522 --> 00:43:48,460
(Tamura) No, I wonder if the other person considers me a friend.

548
00:43:48,526 --> 00:43:51,463
(Ryoko) I wish I could do that too...

549
00:43:51,529 --> 00:43:53,965
(Tamura) Huh?

550
00:43:54,032 --> 00:43:56,034
(Ryoko) No.

551
00:43:57,535 --> 00:43:59,904
>> \Maido! / (Bubbly) Yes.

552
00:43:59,971 --> 00:44:01,406
what? this.

553
00:44:01,473 --> 00:44:03,908
(Bubbly) Mom made a huge purchase in Osaka.

554
00:44:03,975 --> 00:44:06,911
Mom, when are you going to work? (Bubbly) Come on.

555
00:44:06,978 --> 00:44:10,415
Hahaha... That person is free.

556
00:44:10,482 --> 00:44:12,917
Yes, free and whimsical →

557
00:44:12,984 --> 00:44:14,919
I have no idea what you're thinking →

558
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:16,921
Mom's charm.

559
00:44:16,988 --> 00:44:21,426
But... I think about it sometimes.

560
00:44:21,493 --> 00:44:24,429
One day, suddenly, don't tell anyone anything →

561
00:44:24,496 --> 00:44:27,499
I'm afraid it will disappear.

562
00:44:29,501 --> 00:44:32,437
(Luna) Hello, I just arrived.

563
00:44:32,504 --> 00:44:35,006
>> Yes, I found it.

564
00:44:37,008 --> 00:44:39,944
Ah... hello.

565
00:44:40,011 --> 00:44:42,013
(Luna) Hello.
